<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1452,1972,2071]" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,2008,2034]" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">Notes:—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[294,430,2008,2035]" pageId="18" pageNumber="229" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref30080" refString="Luer, C. A. (2009) Miscellaneous new species in Pleurothallidinae (Orchidaceae). Selbyana 30: 1 - 71." type="journal article" year="2009">Luer (2009)</bibRefCitation>
described the narrow, needle-like leaves of this species as unique in the genus. However, similar leaves are now also known to be found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pupulin, Bogarin &amp; Fernandez" authorityYear="2010" box="[696,834,2045,2070]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="18" pageNumber="229" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sotoanus">
<emphasis box="[696,834,2045,2070]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">M. sotoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described in 2010 (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1154,2044,2071]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,190,1853]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Leaf variation in Myoxanthus species.A. Myoxanthus cereus. B. M. parahybunensis. C. M. colothrix. D. M. hirsuticaulis. E. M. congestus. F. M. trachychlamys. G. M. sotoanus. H. M. scandens. Scale bar = 5 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5425743/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
). This species is similar to
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[136,1451,158,220]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[136,277,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[136,277,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[331,484,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellius">
<emphasis box="[331,484,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. pennellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="2009" box="[541,717,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aciculifolius">
<emphasis box="[541,717,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. aciculifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the long-ciliate margins of the middle lobe of the lip.
</paragraph>
